<h1>Trixionary</h1>

<p class="lead">The Trixionary is an online catalog to structure and
	organize movement skills.</p>


<div class="row">
	<div class="col-md-8">
		<h2>Features</h2>

		<ul>
			<li>Catalog skills with the following properties:
				<ul>
					<li>Informative:
						<ul>
							<li>Name and alternative Names</li>
							<li>Short Description</li>
							<li>History and background information</li>
						</ul>
					</li>
					<li>Movement traits:
						<ul>
							<li>Detailied description with sequence picture</li>
							<li>Start- and end positions</li>
							<li>Cyclic or Acyclic movements</li>
							<li>Translation and rotation parameters</li>
						</ul>
					</li>
					<li>Relationships:
						<ul>
							<li>Variations</li>
							<li>Parents and childs</li>
							<li>Multiples</li>
							<li>Composites</li>
						</ul>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</li>
			<li>Multimedia support
				<ul>
					<li>Pictures</li>
					<li>Videos (Youtube and Vimeo integration)</li>
					<li>Tutorials (as videos)</li>
				</ul>
			</li>
			<li>Graph</li>
			<li>Transitions</li>
			<li>Group skills</li>
		</ul>
		
		<h3>Planned features</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>Movement models:
				<ul>
					<li>Phasestructur by Meinel &amp; Schnabel</li>
					<li>Functionphases by GÃ¶hner</li>
					<li>k-Struktur by Kassat</li>
				</ul>
			</li>
			<li>Training support:
				<ul>
					<li>Methodical exercise sequences</li>
					<li>Exercises</li>
					<li>Mistakes</li>
					<li>Technical criterion</li>
					<li>Tester app (for usage in gyms)</li>
				</ul>
			</li>
			<li>Multilanguage support</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
	<div class="col-md-4">
		<h2>Sports</h2>

		<ul class="list-unstyled">
			{% for sport in sports %}
			<li><a href="{{ locations.app_url }}/{% if not sport.getIsDefault() %}{{ sport.getSlug() }}{% endif %}">{{ sport.getTitle() }}</a></li>
			{% endfor %}
		</ul>
	</div>
</div>